[
    {
        "content": "<p>I started attempting this in <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/18426\">#18426</a>; unfortunately a lot of downstream theory relies on many LinearIndependent theorems holding for semirings, presumably bringing with it analogous nonsense</p>",
        "id": 479591418,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1730251422
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>2 messages were moved here from <a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"217875\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/.E2.9C.94.20.02klzzwxh.3A0000.03.20and.20.02klzzwxh.3A0001.03.20isomorphic.20.3D.3E.20.02klzzwxh.3A0002.03\">#Is there code for X? &gt; âœ” <code>E/L/F</code> and <code>K/L'/F</code> isomorphic =&gt; <code>[E:L]=[K:L']</code></a> by <span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"310045\">Eric Wieser</span>.</p>",
        "id": 479598614,
        "sender_full_name": "Notification Bot",
        "timestamp": 1730256742
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Now merged, I guess now the question is whether <code>Module.rank S S = 1</code> holds for some class of semirings</p>",
        "id": 479672726,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1730291756
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What do you have in mind? It's <a href=\"https://mathoverflow.net/questions/317422/rings-that-fail-to-satisfy-the-strong-rank-condition\">unknown</a> whether it always fails for rings failing StrongRankCondition.</p>",
        "id": 479682423,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1730294864
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Probably a fun exercise: for a nontrivial semiring R and an infinite type Î¹, let <code>A := Module.End R (Î¹ â†’â‚€ R)</code>. Construct <code>A â‰ƒâ‚—[A] Î¹ â†’â‚€ A</code> and deduce that <code>#Î¹ â‰¤ Module.rank A A</code>. (I'm not sure when the equality holds.)</p>",
        "id": 479684502,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1730295455
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Mainly just something that works for Nat, NNRat, and NNReal</p>",
        "id": 479689903,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1730297023
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hopefully those all satisfy <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=StrongRankCondition#doc\">docs#StrongRankCondition</a>, but I don't think mathlib knows that</p>",
        "id": 479690073,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1730297068
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, I think you can consider localizations of their additive monoids, endow them with ring structures, which will be isomorphic to Int, Rat, and Real respectively. (Will also need this to put ring structure on <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>K</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">K_0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">â€‹</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>.) The LocalizationMap will be injective if the additive monoid is cancellative. These are commutative rings so they satisfy StrongRankCondition. There is <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=AddSubmonoid.LocalizationMap.map_injective_of_injective#doc\">docs#AddSubmonoid.LocalizationMap.map_injective_of_injective</a> but we need a more general statement and we need to show the <code>map</code> is linear.</p>",
        "id": 479722582,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1730306095
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"224323\">Junyan Xu</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/116395-maths/topic/Linear.20independence.20over.20semirings/near/479722582\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>can consider localizations of their additive monoids</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=AddOreLocalization#doc\">docs#AddOreLocalization</a> ? Will they always have a ring structure?</p>",
        "id": 480084984,
        "sender_full_name": "Jz Pan",
        "timestamp": 1730480165
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah I'm claiming <code>AddLocalization (âŠ¤ : AddSubmonoid R)</code> is a ring if R is a semiring.</p>",
        "id": 480090862,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1730482474
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We probably need to come up with a proper IsAddLocalization predicate, as Int isn't defeq to AddLocalizaiton of Nat, etc.</p>",
        "id": 480091516,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1730482736
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"224323\">Junyan Xu</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/116395-maths/topic/Linear.20independence.20over.20semirings/near/480091516\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We probably need to come up with a proper IsAddLocalization predicate, as Int isn't defeq to AddLocalizaiton of Nat, etc.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Does <code>@[to_additive]</code> works for <code>IsLocalization</code> -&gt; <code>IsAddLocalization</code>?</p>",
        "id": 480097565,
        "sender_full_name": "Jz Pan",
        "timestamp": 1730485473
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There is already <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=AddSubmonoid.LocalizationMap#doc\">docs#AddSubmonoid.LocalizationMap</a>, but we at least want to assume it's a multiplicative homomorphism as well. Looks like no additional constraints are necessary.</p>",
        "id": 480098809,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1730486066
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"224323\">Junyan Xu</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/116395-maths/topic/Linear.20independence.20over.20semirings/near/480090862\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Yeah I'm claiming <code>AddLocalization (âŠ¤ : AddSubmonoid R)</code> is a ring if R is a semiring.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I realized that <code>â„¤ âŠ—[â„•] R</code> is a readily available construction soon after I wrote <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/18744#issuecomment-2512805912\">this comment</a>. Maybe we should introduce an Algebra version of <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/RingTheory/IsTensorProduct.html#IsTensorProduct\">IsTensorProduct</a>?</p>",
        "id": 486592210,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1733518123
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, I think an algebra version is a good idea.</p>",
        "id": 486931907,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1733732715
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Isn't <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Algebra.IsPushout#doc\">docs#Algebra.IsPushout</a> this Algebra version?</p>",
        "id": 487010198,
        "sender_full_name": "Christian Merten",
        "timestamp": 1733754642
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Good find! There's a drawback of formulating everything in terms of Algebra though, which is that you must assume S and R' are commutative. In our setting R is N, S is Z but R' can be an arbitrary semiring.</p>\n<p>Even for commutative semirings I think we might still need the AddLocalization construction, just like we access some properties of the tensor product with a localized ring by the explicit construction of localized modules, e.g. that's how we prove flatness of localization.</p>\n<p>Anyway, this is something hopefully true and one might try to prove:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">RingTheory</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">IsTensorProduct</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">CommSemiring</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">CommRing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Algebra</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Algebra</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">IsPushout</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">â„•</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">â„¤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">â†”</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">âˆƒ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">âŠ¤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">AddSubmonoid</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">LocalizationMap</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">toFun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">algebraMap</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 487056271,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1733765370
    },
    {
