    {
        "content": "<p>It's probably GitHub's bug; the branch name under the PR title is also crossed out, and Refined GitHub no longer creates a \"merge master\" button at the bottom so I have to create a PR for that.<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/p3QH1Y_LtFx-AeW5Xq3rwQzR/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/p3QH1Y_LtFx-AeW5Xq3rwQzR/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img data-original-dimensions=\"1294x183\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/3121/p3QH1Y_LtFx-AeW5Xq3rwQzR/image.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div><blockquote>\n<p>Note that github will close <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/20497\">#20497</a> once it's target branch is closed by bors.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>It seems that a bot now automatically change the target branch to master? But it doesn't automatically reopen the PR. I had to <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/20247#event-15764821069\">manually change</a> the base branch 2 weeks ago (and before doing that I needed to temporarily restore the merged/deleted branch).</p>",
